div.p:
[Here follow discussion of current relations with the Republic of China;
                            a discussion of the merits of granting a loan to Mexico’s national oil
                            company, Petroleos Mexicanos; a review of Secretary Dulles’ draft of a speech he planned to
                            deliver to the Foreign Policy Association in New York on February 16;
                            and a determination to invite Prime Minister U Nu of Burma to visit the United States in June.]
